    <h3>Building The Earthquake Tool</h3>
    <p class="prepend-1">
    -- <%= link_to "Download this zip", earthquakesource_path%> containing the necessary images, sources files, and CMakeList file.
    <br/>
    -- Extract to some directory with no spaces. Preferably in the same folder that VTK, VTKBuild, and VTKData are in.
    <br/>
    -- Open CMake and choose the source directory and binary directory to be the folder you just extracted.
    <br/>
    -- Click configure, make sure to choose Visual Studio 10, not Visual Studio 10 Win64.
    <br/>
    -- Set the CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX path to something without spaces again.
    <br/>
    -- If CMake couldn't find VTKBuild directory set it manually
    <br/>
    -- Click configure again, and then click generate.
    <br/>
    -- Open the AllBuild Visual Studio Project. 
    <br/>
    -- Inside Visual Studio, right click on AllBuild and select Build.
    <br/>
    -- Right click on the RenderWindowUI Project and select "set as startup project".
    <br/>
    -- Build it and run it.
    <h3>You should have a working copy of the earthquake project</h3>
    </p>
