    <h3>Building The Lake Michigan Tool</h3>
    <p class="prepend-1">
       -- To download the source code <%= link_to "click here.", "http://renaissancesoftware.net/paulgrenning/LakeMichiganSource.zip"%>
        <br/>
       -- To download the data to use with the program <%= link_to "click here.", "http://renaissancesoftware.net/paulgrenning/LakeMichiganData.zip"%>
    <br/>
    -- Extract the source code to some directory with no spaces. Preferably in the same folder that VTK, VTKBuild, and VTKData are in.
    <br/>
    -- Open CMake and choose the source directory and binary directory to be the folder you just extracted.
    <br/>
    -- Click configure, make sure to choose Visual Studio 10, not Visual Studio 10 Win64.
    <br/>
    -- Set the CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX path to something without spaces again.
    <br/>
    -- If CMake couldn't find VTKBuild directory set it manually
    <br/>
    -- Click configure again, and then click generate.
    <br/>
    -- Open the AllBuild Visual Studio Project. 
    <br/>
    -- Inside Visual Studio, right click on AllBuild and select Build.
    <br/>
    -- Extract the data from the LakeMichiganData.zip that you should have downloaded. Take the three folders labeled 2006Data, 2010Data, Jun-18-2010Data and the file labled crm_great_lakesMedium.nc and place it in the project directory.
    <br/>
    -- Right click on the RenderWindowUI Project and select "set as startup project".
    <br/>
    -- Build it and run it.
    <h3>You should have a working copy of the Lake Michigan project</h3>
    </p>
